    Key insights (per the agent prompt):
      1. THIS TASK IS THE RESOLVE-BLOCKER ANCHOR. Combined with sibling
         task 02 (Closed) on the same case 03, the pair demonstrates
         that the resolve gate fires when ANY child task is non-Closed
         (specifically THIS Open task). The validate_resolved_
         transition subflow's GlideRecord query against
         x_casemgmt_case_task where case=case_03 AND status != Closed
         returns EXACTLY ONE row (THIS task) and aborts the
         In Progress -> Resolved transition on case 03 with the
         verbatim error "All tasks must be closed before resolving
         this case." per AAP Section 0.7.4.
      2. THE STATUS Open (Title Case) matches the choice list and is
         the EXACT comparand value for the resolve-gate's GlideRecord
         query addQuery('status', '!=', 'Closed') - any case variant
         ("open", "OPEN", "OpEn") would either fail the choice
         dictionary validation OR (if accepted somehow) would not
         match the exact string comparison performed by the gate's
         query, producing incorrect resolve behavior.
      3. THE TYPE Investigation IS THE MOST THEMATIC for early-
         lifecycle work on a case under investigation. The case is
         "In Progress" because the agent is actively investigating;
         this task tracks that work. Investigation is the first of
         four task type Choice values (Investigation, Review,
         Follow-up, Other), positioned to capture the body of work
         between case intake and case resolution.
      4. THE due_date IS FUTURE-DATED (+5 days, 2026-05-06). A future
         due_date excludes this task from the "My Overdue Tasks"
         widget on the Agent Workspace dashboard (filter:
         due_date < Today AND status != Closed). This task IS in the
         "My Open Tasks" surface (status != Closed AND assigned_to =
         current user) but NOT in the "My Overdue Tasks" surface (due
         date qualifier not satisfied). The +5 day window is the
         negative-test fixture for the My Overdue Tasks widget,
         demonstrating that the report's date filter excludes future-
         dated active tasks rather than flagging them as overdue.
      5. THE <case> REFERENCE USES display_value=CASE0000003. This is
         the predictable auto-generated number when cases are loaded
         in order on a fresh PDI per AAP Section 0.5.2. The inner
         text equals the display_value (CASE0000003) for canonical-
         key resolution; the resolve mechanism on a fresh PDI is
         "find x_casemgmt_case where number = CASE0000003" performed
         at import time by the platform.
      6. THE Date FORMAT IS YYYY-MM-DD. Per AAP Section 0.5.7,
         due_date is a Date, NOT a DateTime. ServiceNow's GlideDate
         accepts this ISO-8601 format with no time component.
         Including a time component or timezone suffix would either
         fail validation or be silently truncated, both of which are
         undesirable for the demo fixture.
      7. THE DETERMINISTIC sys_id (md5 hash of the subject string
         "Demo task 01: Investigate request scope" =
         52bf35d626cf81334c73e397f63522d8) ensures idempotent re-
         imports per AAP Section 0.7.1 round-trip-verification. If
         this record is re-imported (e.g., during the round-trip-
         verify validation gate), the platform recognizes the
         existing sys_id and applies action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE" by
         updating the existing record in place rather than creating
         a duplicate. The hash input is the literal subject string;
         the resulting hex value is exactly 32 lowercase hexadecimal
         characters as required by the sys_id contract.
      8. NO <priority>, <percent_complete>, <details>, <pending_status>,
         OR OTHER ArkCase-only fields. The minimum 6-field set
         (case, subject, type, status, assigned_to, due_date) is
         strictly enforced per the AAP Section 0.5.7 verbatim
         definition. Bloating the schema with additional fields is
         forbidden by the MINIMAL CHANGE CLAUSE in AAP Section 0.7.2.
         Per the source-side semantic reference at
         acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-task-plugin/src/main/java/
         com/armedia/acm/plugins/task/model/AcmTask.java, ArkCase's
         AcmTask entity has approximately 60 fields (taskId, priority,
         title with @Size(min=1) validation, dueDate with @NotNull,
         attachedToObjectType, attachedToObjectName, attachedToObjectId,
         assignee, owner, businessProcessName, businessProcessId,
         adhocTask, completed, status, pendingStatus, percentComplete,
         details, type, createDate, taskStartDate, taskFinishedDate,
         taskDurationInMillis, workflowRequestType, workflowRequestId,
         reviewDocumentPdfRenditionId, reviewDocumentFormXmlId,
         documentUnderReview, documentsToReview, childObjects,
         reworkInstructions, outcomeName, participants, notification
         receivers, ECM container, parent metadata, candidate claim
         groups, next assignee, legacy system ID, buckslip approval
         data, and restriction flags). The ServiceNow target replicates
         ONLY 6 of those fields, mapped as: ArkCase title (@Size(min=1))
         -> ServiceNow subject (Mandatory String(255)), ArkCase dueDate
         (@NotNull Date) -> ServiceNow due_date (Mandatory Date),
         ArkCase assignee (free-form String) -> ServiceNow assigned_to
         (Reference to sys_user), ArkCase status (free-form String) ->
         ServiceNow status (Choice: Open, In Progress, Closed),
         ArkCase type (free-form String) -> ServiceNow type (Choice:
         Investigation, Review, Follow-up, Other), ArkCase
         attachedToObjectId -> ServiceNow case (Reference to
         x_casemgmt_case). The remaining ~54 fields are out of scope
         per AAP Section 0.3.2 (Outlook/Activiti/ECM/Buckslip
         integrations) or replaced by ServiceNow platform features
         (sys_created_on subsumes createDate; sys_updated_on subsumes
         taskFinishedDate for closed tasks; auto-numbering subsumes
         taskId).
      9. THE BUILD AGENT COMPUTES due_date DYNAMICALLY at file-
         generation time so that the relative offset (+5 days) is
         preserved across importation timeframes. The actual stored
         value (2026-05-06) is the static result of today + 5 days
         evaluated at this file's generation time (today = 2026-05-01
         per the build environment date).
     10. THE VERBATIM ERROR MESSAGE "All tasks must be closed before
         resolving this case." MUST appear (per AAP Section 0.7.4)
         when the operator attempts case 03 -> Resolved while THIS
         task is Open. The error message string is owned by the
         validate_resolved_transition subflow (and the
         CaseTransitionValidator Script Include); this task record
         merely contributes the row that triggers the error path.
     11. THE casemgmt PLACEHOLDER IS PRESERVED VERBATIM in
         sys_class_name, sys_update_name, sys_scope, sys_package,
         all reference display_values that include the scope prefix
         (assigned_to display_value), and the file path. The
         placeholder is intended for downstream substitution by the
         build pipeline at the time of PDI scope assignment - the
         substitution is global across the entire scoped application
         output (every file under servicenow-case-management-poc/).
